content: Nate Diaz is a professional mixed martial artist known for his time in the UFC. Before joining the UFC, Diaz competed in World Extreme Cagefighting, Strikeforce, and Pancrase. He has the third highest number of UFC bonus awards, with 16 in total. Born and raised in Stockton, California, Diaz comes from a mixed Mexican and Anglo heritage and began training in martial arts with his brother, Nick, at the age of 11.
